def: Infested by weevils; as, weeviled grain. [Written alsoweevilled.]
One who holds to no particular creed or dogma.
One who looks. Looker-on, a spectator; one that looks on, buthas no agency or part in an affair.Did not this fatal war affront thy coast, Yet sattest thou an idlelooker-on Fairfax.
A heap or heaps of rubbish or refuse.
Of or pertaining to a cynosure.

Having a stomach that is easily or nauseated; hence, nice toexcess in taste; fastidious; easily disgusted; apt to be offended attrifling improprieties.Quoth he, that honor's very squeamish That takes a basting for ablemish. Hudibras.His muse is rustic, and perhaps too plain The men of squeamish tasteto entertain. Southern.So ye grow squeamish, Gods, and sniff at heaven. M. Arnold.
The principal bone of the shoulder girdle in mammals; theshoulder blade.
In the game of three-card loo, an extra hand, dealt on thetable, which may be substituted for the hand dealt to a player.
